This paper is primarily focused on image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the learning behavior of CNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The visual-analytics methods used in the paper can also be applied to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
